Deputy President, William Ruto, has reiterated the government’s commitment to taking proactive measures to accelerate gender equality and women’s empowerment, further stating that the government would do everything possible to ensure women achieve their fair share of leadership positions in the country. Ruto who was last night attending a dinner event hosted by the Federation of Women Lawyers, FIDA, said he was confident parliament would soon pass the two thirds gender bill to ensure the country heeds to the constitutional demands. The government has meanwhile already rapidly expanded the availability of funding for women enterprises through the women enterprise fund, UWEZO fund and Affirmative Action fund. 